<div id="review_2103335441" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2103335441" />
    <a title="Bookish Picks" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70742672-bookish-picks"><img alt="Bookish Picks" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1534163745p2/70742672.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2103335441?book_show_action=true">Aug 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bookish Picks" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bookish Picks" href="/user/show/70742672-bookish-picks">Bookish Picks</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2103335441" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10528112030000072853">Love Story by Samantha Chandler&apos;s is such an inspiring memoir, that left me with the message that people can really achieve great things, no matter where they come from. You can go through difficult things and emerge from the other side stronger than before. From her humble beginnings in Louisiana, Samantha finds herself on the top rung of society, only for that life to crash completely. From the ruins of that life, she found her faith, which gave her the strength to reconnect with her children </span>
  <span id="freeText10528112030000072853" style="display:none">Love Story by Samantha Chandler's is such an inspiring memoir, that left me with the message that people can really achieve great things, no matter where they come from. You can go through difficult things and emerge from the other side stronger than before. From her humble beginnings in Louisiana, Samantha finds herself on the top rung of society, only for that life to crash completely. From the ruins of that life, she found her faith, which gave her the strength to reconnect with her children and find capacity to feel such love and joy.<br /><br />As memoirs go, this one was one of the better ones I have read. It's style was informal and relaxed, but it was truthful and real to. I felt a connection with the author once I finished, and I certainly will be reading more from Samantha Chandler in the future.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10528112030000072853" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


